dward+Wright+%28mathematician%29&amp;rft.atitle=Logarithm&amp;rft.au=J.W.L.G.&amp;rft.btitle=The+Encyclop%C3%A6dia+Britannica&amp;rft.date=1910%2F1911&amp;rft.edition=11th&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.1911encyclopedia.org%2FLogarithm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot"><span title="&#160;Dead link since July 2016">dead link</span></a></i>]</span></sup></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Parish register, London, St. Dionis Backchurch, 2 December 1615, GL [burial]: see Apt, "Wright, Edward", <i><a href="/wiki/Dictionary_of_National_Biography" title="Dictionary of National Biography">Oxford Dictionary of National Biography</a></i>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Lewi, "Mercator, Wright and Mapmaking", p. 31.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFWillebrord_Snellius1624" class="citation"><a href="/wiki/Willebrord_Snellius" title="Willebrord Snellius">Willebrord Snellius</a> (1624), <i>Willebrordi Snellii \xc3\xa0 Royen Tiphys Batavus, sive histiodromice, de navium cursibus et re navali. (Tabul\xc3\xa6 canonic\xc3\xa6 parallelorum Canones loxodromici \xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xce\xbf\xcf\x87\xce\xb5\xce\xb9\xcf\x81\xce\xbf\xce\xb9.) Willebrord Snellius van Royen; The Batavian Tiphys; or Navigation, Ships\' Courses and Naval Matters. (Canonical Tables of Parallels, Handy Loxodromic Tables.)</i>, <a href="/wiki/Leiden" title="Leiden">Leiden</a>: Ex officin\xc3\xa2 